        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the waffle iron. Whisk together the sourdough discard, milk, eggs, melted butter, and vanilla extract in a large bowl until smooth. Add the flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt and whisk briefly until just combined. Do not overmix; a few small lumps are fine. The batter should be pourable but not watery.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Lightly oil or butter the waffle iron if it is not non-stick. Pour in enough batter to just fill the grid, close, and cook for 3 to 5 minutes until golden and crisp, and the iron stops steaming. Do not open early. Transfer to a rack or a low oven while you cook the remaining waffles. Serve with butter and maple syrup, or with fresh fruit and cream.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
